en.achievements:
CCIs is a strategic sector in participating regions and can play an important role in the transition towards the EU green deal and urban sustainability. ChIMERA + transferred ChIMERA process and tools for the growth of CCIs promoting the sustainable urban development in Zaragoza, Nova Gorica and Sarajevo areas. In particular, the transferring process was focused on the following steps:

1.	Analysis of the CCI sector in Zaragoza, Nova Gorica and Sarajevo carried out by receiver partners (SARGA, SERDA, MoNG) under mentoring of giver partners (RAFVG and Creative Apulia Cluster) in cooperation with local stakeholders of CCI sector;

2.	Analysis of 3 frontrunners, following the methodology tested in ChIMERA: giver partners transferred the methodology and supported the other partners in both the selection of the frontrunners and the analysis, while SARGA, SERDA and MoNG carried out the analysis. This activity allowed the exchange of good practices and lessons learnt, providing useful hints for the receiver areas; 

3.	Implementation of a Capacity building action through 4 workshops on best practices, innovation and visions related to the role of CCIs in urban and sustainable transition. Creative Apulia Cluster organised the workshops with the support of RAFVG; SARGA,SERDA,MoNG and their main stakeholders were the direct beneficiaries. All the actors involved acquired know how based on the experiences and good practices presented and discussed during the capacity building seminars. To better know how other countries and stakeholders deals with CCIs and urban sustainability was an added value for all participating regions;

4.	Outlining action plans of the receiver areas by SARGA,SERDA,MoNG with the support RAFVG that set the methodology based on ChIMERA experience and supervised the activity. Moreover, the activity involved the main stakeholders of Zaragoza, Nova Gorica and Sarajevo. Developed action plans are strategic documents to foster the role of CCIs in the transition process towards a urban sustainability and to support the development of local CCI sector and can be adopted by the competent institutions; 

5.	Development of guidelines for the policy makers to support CCIs and its role in the urban sustainability: the document was produced by RAFVG capitalizing ChIMERA and ChIMERA plus experiences and shared among the partnershipLast, another important result of CHIMERA+ was the establishment of transnational networks among project partners and stakeholders.
